Naming of Methods

All method names follow Java camelCase and use descriptive verb phrases as recommended:

checkWebsite(), checkAllWebsites() – clearly communicate the action performed
notifyObservers(), attach(), detach() – standard Observer pattern vocabulary
addSubscription(), deleteSubscription() – follow domain-specific naming
setStrategy(), compare(snapshot1, snapshot2) – reflect the Strategy pattern intent
fetchContent(), compareSnapshots() – self-documenting, no abbreviations



Naming of Classes

All class names use PascalCase and describe the entity they represent:

WebsiteMonitor, SubscriptionController – noun phrases indicating role
ContentSizeStrategy, HtmlContentStrategy, TextContentStrategy – clearly communicate the algorithm variant



Structural Organisation

The project is separated into logical packages reflecting different responsibilities:

model – data classes (Website, User, Subscription)
controller – application logic (WebsiteMonitor, SubscriptionController)
notification – output classes (Notification, Email, SMS)
strategy – comparison algorithms (Strategy interface + 3 implementations)

This separation supports Separation of Concerns (SoC) and High Cohesion from GRASP.

Packages are now with all-lowercase package names.
